James de Villiers, News24 (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; The alleged mastermind behind the theft of 15 computers from the Office of the Chief Justice has been taken into police custody, a police spokesperson has confirmed. Acting Police commissioner spokesperson Athlenda Mathe told News24 that Nkosinathi Msimango reported to the police station on Friday. She could not yet say whether he had handed himself over to police or if he had been apprehended.More to follow.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.